3. SAFETY REQUIREMENTS. Any deployment of the Software in systems that
   interact with humans or make decisions affecting human welfare must
   include appropriate safety controls, including but not limited to:
   (a) Input and output safety gates
   (b) Human oversight mechanisms
   (c) Audit logging of decisions
   (d) The ability to halt autonomous operation

4. HIGH-RISK DOMAINS. Use of the Software in safety-critical domains
   (healthcare, autonomous vehicles, critical infrastructure, law
   enforcement, military) requires separate written permission and
   must include domain-appropriate safety and governance controls.

5. AUTONOMOUS OPERATION. The Software must not be deployed for fully
   autonomous operation without human oversight unless the deployer
   has conducted and documented a safety assessment appropriate to
   the deployment context.

6. ETHICAL USE. The Software must not be used to:
   (a) Cause harm to individuals or groups
   (b) Discriminate on the basis of protected characteristics
   (c) Conduct surveillance without appropriate legal authority
   (d) Generate disinformation or deceptive content
   (e) Circumvent safety controls in other AI systems

